ABREVIATIONS

DATA SOURCES

The data sources used in this analysis will be determined empirically by evaluating the study inputs against pre-computed characterization results. This method generates a rough estimate determining which databases have the information necessary to observe both the outcomes and exposures of interest in the required populations. Only databases that pass data diagnostics will be used in the study.

APPENDIX

Module Versions

The OHDSI Strategus modules used in this study are:

Cohorts

Emergency room visits (0Pe, 0Era)

Cohort Entry Events

People enter the cohort when observing any of the following:

  1. visit occurrences of âEmergency roomâ.

Cohort Exit

The cohort end date will be offset from index eventâs end date plus 0 days.

Cohort Eras

Entry events will be combined into cohort eras if they are within 0 days of each other.

Tuberculosis

Cohort Entry Events

People may enter the cohort when observing any of the following:

  1. condition occurrences of âRespiratory and pulmonary tuberculosisâ.

Inclusion Criteria

1. At least 3 distinct drug eras of TB drugs

Entry events having at least 3 distinct standard concepts from drug eras of âAll TB drugsâ, starting between 0 days before and all days after cohort entry start date.

Cohort Exit

The cohort end date will be offset from index eventâs end date plus 365 days.

Cohort Eras

Entry events will be combined into cohort eras if they are within 0 days of each other.

Systemic lupus erythematosus indexed on signs, symptoms, treatment, or diagnosis (FP)
